 "."}], "source_refs": ["TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n7505", "headword_ar": "حُرٌّ", "root": "Hr", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Free, ingenuous,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "free-born; contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EabodN", "text_ar": "عَبْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K:) fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hur~apN", "text_ar": "حُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) pl. masc."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHoraArN", "text_ar": "اَحْرَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HiraArN", "text_ar": "حِرَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (IJ, K;) not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaraArN", "text_ar": "حَرَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as some say; nor is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HiraArN", "text_ar": "حِرَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "an inf. n. as well as a pl., as others say: (MF:) pl. fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaraAy^iru", "text_ar": "حَرَايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K,) contr. to analogy, and, as Suh says, the only instance of the kind except"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ajarN maraAy^iru", "text_ar": "شَجَرٌ مَرَايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ajarapN mur~apN", "text_ar": "شَجَرَةٌ مُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for the [regular] pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuEolapN", "text_ar": "فُعْلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "foEalN", "text_ar": "فْعَلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hur~apN", "text_ar": "حُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "has this form of pl. because it is syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kariymapN", "text_ar": "كَرِيمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqiylapN", "text_ar": "عَقِيلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as will be seen in what follows]; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mur~apN", "text_ar": "مُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", because it means"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xabiyvapu AlT~aEomi", "text_ar": "خَبِيثَةُ الطَّعْمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) Omar said to the women who used to go forth to the mosque,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA^arud~an~akon~a HaraAy^ira", "text_ar": "لَاَرُدَّنَّكْنَّ حَرَايِرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will assuredly make you to become free women"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will assuredly make you to keep to the houses"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": for the curtain is lowered before free women; not before slavewomen. (TA.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hur~iy~apN", "text_ar": "حُرِّيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Generous, noble,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well-born;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EabodN", "text_ar": "عَبْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used to signify “ ignoble, ” or “ base-born: ” (Mgh:) and so the fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hur~apN", "text_ar": "حُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Mgh, K;) applied to a woman; (TA;) and to a she-camel: (S:) and so the masc. applied to a horse. (K, TA.) [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAtato bilayolapi Hur~apK", "text_ar": "بَاتَتْ بِلَيْلَةِ حُرَّةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She passed a virgin's night"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is said of her whose husband has not been able to devirginate her (S, A, K) in the night when she has been first brought to him: (TA:) because the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hur~ap", "text_ar": "حُرَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is modest and repugnant: (Har p. 418:) in the contr. case one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bilayolapi $ayobaA='a", "text_ar": "بِلَيْلَةِ شَيْبَا=ءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, L:) and one says also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bilayolapK Hur~apK", "text_ar": "بِلَيْلَةٍ حُرَّةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bilayolapK $ayobaA='a", "text_ar": "بِلَيْلَةٍ شَيْبَا=ءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) [And hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layolapu Hur~ap", "text_ar": "لَيْلَةُ حُرَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layolapN Hur~apN", "text_ar": "لَيْلَةٌ حُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signify also (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The first night of the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lunar"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "month"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) its last night is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layolapu $ayobaA='a", "text_ar": "لَيْلَةُ شَيْبَا=ءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layolapN", "text_ar": "لَيْلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ayobaA='u", "text_ar": "شَيْبَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) You say also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wajohN Hur~N", "text_ar": "وَجْهٌ حُرٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  [app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An ingenuous countenance"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Generous,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ingenuous, in conduct"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": as in the saying of Imra-el-Keys,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "laEamoruka maA qalobiY A_ilaY A^aholihi biHoro"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "By thy life, my heart is not generous in conduct to its,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his, companion"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; meaning that it is averse therefrom, and inclines to another. (Az, TA.) [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saHaAbapN Hur~apN", "text_ar": "سَحَابَةٌ حُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A cloud bountiful with rain;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abounding with rain."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  A"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "deed or action. (K, TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maAh`*aA minoka biHur~K", "text_ar": "مَاهٰذَا مِنْكَ بِحُرٍّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is not good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well, of thee."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  Anything"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "excel-lent;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as poetry, &c. (TA.) You say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalaAmN Hur~N", "text_ar": "كَلَامٌ حُرٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  [app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "excellent, speech"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "language"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "earth, or clay, and sand: (K, TA:) or earth, or clay,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in which is no sand"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, A:) and sand"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in which is no earth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "clay"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) or sand"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that has good herbage"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (A:) you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ramolapN Hur~apN", "text_ar": "رَمْلَةٌ حُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, A;) and the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaraAy^iru", "text_ar": "حَرَايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) or sand"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in which is no mixture of any other thing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb: [accord. to which, this is the primary meaning of the word, whence the meaning of “ free, ” i. e. the “ contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EabodN", "text_ar": "عَبْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": ” but accord. to the A and TA, it is tropical:]) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroDN Hur~apN", "text_ar": "اَرْضٌ حُرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "land in which is no salt earth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (A:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in which is no sand"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": as applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that upon which no tithe is levied,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it is post-classical. (Mgh.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "middle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, K,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "best part,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,) of sand, (S, K, TA,) and of a house. (S, A, TA.) ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "best"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of anything; (K, TA;) as, for instance, of fruit. (TA.) ―         -b9-  Also sing. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHoraAr", "text_ar": "اَحْرَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the term"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHoraAru Albuquwli", "text_ar": "اَحْرَارُ البُقُولِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) which means (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Herbs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "leguminous plants, that are eaten without being cooked;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A;) as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albuquwli", "text_ar": "البُقُولِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hur~iy~apu", "text_ar": "حُرِّيَّةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (A:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as are slender and succulent;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*ukuwru", "text_ar": "ذُكُورُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albuquwli", "text_ar": "البُقُولِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means “ such as are thick and rough: ” (AHeyth:) or the former are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as are slender and soft;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the latter, “ such as are hard and thick: ” (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "E$b", "text_ar": "عشب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) or the former are"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 539}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as are slender and sweet;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the latter, “ such as are thick, and inclining to bitterness: ” (TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*kr", "text_ar": "ذكر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) or the former are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as are rough;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and these are three, namely,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~afalu", "text_ar": "النَّفَلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHurobuvu", "text_ar": "الحُرْبُثُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlqafoEaA='u", "text_ar": "القَفْعَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHur~u", "text_ar": "الحُرُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a plant of the kind called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~ajiyl", "text_ar": "النَّجِيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "growing in salt grounds."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hur~u Alwajohi", "text_ar": "حُرُّ الوَجْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What appears of the face"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what appears of the elevated part of the cheek;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;) [i. e.] the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ball,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "most prominent place, of the cheek;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(W p. 28;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHur~apu", "text_ar": "الحُرَّةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the same,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the elevated part of the cheek"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) or the former is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what fronts one, of the face:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the four tracks of the tears, from each corner of each eye."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laTamahu EalaY Hur~i wajohihi", "text_ar": "لَطَمَهُ عَلَى حُرِّ وَجْهِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He slapped him on the ball of his cheek"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, TA. *)       -A2-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "young one of a gazelle."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.) ―         -b2-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "young one of a serpent:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a slender serpent:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or it is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a slender serpent, like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAn~", "text_ar": "جَانّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a white colour:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a white serpent:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a serpent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "absolutely. (TA.) ―         -b3-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "young one of a pigeon:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "male thereof."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAqu Hur~K", "text_ar": "سَاقُ حُرٍّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[is said to signify] The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "male of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qamaAriY~", "text_ar": "قَمَارِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kind of collared turtle-doves of which the female is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qumoriy~ap", "text_ar": "قُمْرِيَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qumoriY~N", "text_ar": "قُمْرِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")]: (S, Msb, K:) Homeyd Ibn-Thowr says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "wamaA haAja h`*aA Al$~awoqa A_il~aA HamaAmapN\n                      \n                     \n                        daEato saAqa Hur~K taroHapF wataran~umaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And nothing excited this desire but a pigeon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HamaAmN", "text_ar": "حَمَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sAq Hr~", "text_ar": "ساق حرّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sorrowing and warbling"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: or, accord. to IJ, the right reading is"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "daEato saAqa Hur~K fiY HamaAmK taran~umaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sAq Hr~", "text_ar": "ساق حرّ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "among"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "other"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pigeons, warbling"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: but some say that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlsAq", "text_ar": "الساق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the pigeon;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hr~", "text_ar": "حرّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its young one:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sAq Hr~", "text_ar": "ساق حرّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cry of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qmArY~", "text_ar": "قمارىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and is an onomatopœia: accord. to Aboo- 'Adnán, it is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sAq Har~", "text_ar": "ساق حَرّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and means the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "warbling of the pigeon:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and Sakhr El-Gheí makes it a compound, and indecl.; using the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tunaAdiY", "text_ar": "تُنَادِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAqa Hur~a", "text_ar": "سَاقَ حُرَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "she calls"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sAq Hr~", "text_ar": "ساق حرّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: on which IJ observes, As says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sAq Hr~", "text_ar": "ساق حرّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is thought to mean the young one of the bird; but it is her"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cry:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and he (IJ) adds, the fact that the poet [Sakhr] does not make it decl. is an evidence of the correctness of the assertion of As; for, were it decl., he would have said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saAqa Hur~K", "text_ar": "سَاقَ حُرٍّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "if it consisted of two nouns whereof the former was prefixed to the other so as to govern it in the gen. case, or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sAq Hur~FA", "text_ar": "ساق حُرًّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "if it were a compound; as it is indeterminate: and its being made decl. by Homeyd does not show it to be not significant of a sound; for sometimes an expression significant of a sound consists of t